<ul>
  <li>The above code for MongoDB 3.6 with latest ruby driver <code class="highlighter-rouge">upsert</code> doesnâ€™t return <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/13955212/check-if-mongodb-upsert-did-an-insert-or-an-update/13955778">updatedExisting</a> boolean instead it returns <code class="highlighter-rouge">nModified</code>: <code class="highlighter-rouge">1</code> for update, <code class="highlighter-rouge">0</code> for insert</li>
